body_html:
I don't think this is an error with TF.

(-.4)^(-.4) and (-.4)^(.4) will not give answers in the range of real numbers so NaN is a reasonable result. To convince yourself of why, try to reason out what tf.pow(-1, .5) should print? Or put it more simply, what is the square root of -1?
